medical_qa.question: Does mechanical limitation of pulmonary blood flow facilitate heart transplantation in older infants with hypoplastic left heart syndrome?
medical_qa.normalized_answer: Pre-transplant mechanical limitation of pulmonary blood flow simplified management and reduced morbidity for HLHS patients undergoing heart transplantation at ages >or=4 months.

medical_qa.question: Is the Jarvik 2000 associated with less infections than the HeartMate left ventricular assist device?
medical_qa.normalized_answer: Implantation of the Jarvik 2000 is associated with less device-related infections than the HeartMate-LVAD.

medical_qa.question: Does Removal of YY1 binding sites in HPV 16 LCR increase viral transforming activities on mouse fibroblasts?
medical_qa.normalized_answer: Removal of YY1 binding motifs in HPV 16 LCR can increase the anchorage-independent growth ability and transforming capacity of HPV 16 on mouse fibroblasts.

medical_qa.question: Are red cell and plasma plant sterols related during consumption of plant stanol and sterol ester spreads in children with hypercholesterolemia?
medical_qa.normalized_answer: Plant sterols increase and plant stanols decrease the ratios of plant sterols to cholesterol in red cells of hypercholesterolemic children proportionately to the changes in plasma.

medical_qa.question: Does interleukin-10 inhibit inducible nitric oxide synthase in an animal model of necrotizing enterocolitis?
medical_qa.normalized_answer: IL-10 suppresses iNOS mRNA and nitric oxide expression in an experimental model of NEC.

medical_qa.question: Does Chronic Helicobacter pylori infection induce apoptosis-resistance in gastric epithelial cells?
medical_qa.normalized_answer: Chronic H.pylori infection induces apoptosis resistance in gastric epithelial cells.

medical_qa.question: Does training improve divers' ability to detect increased CO2?
medical_qa.normalized_answer: CO2 recognition training improves the diver's capability to detect CO2. Poor CO2 detection and CO2 retention may increase the risk of CNS-oxygen toxicity in divers.

medical_qa.question: Does combined skin prick and patch testing enhance identification of peanut-allergic patients with atopic dermatitis?
medical_qa.normalized_answer: APTs with peanuts may be a useful addition to standard testing for diagnosing peanut allergy in atopic dermatitis patients.

medical_qa.question: Does direct contact between human peripheral blood mononuclear cells and renal fibroblasts facilitate the expression of monocyte chemoattractant protein-1?
medical_qa.normalized_answer: The interaction between renal fibroblasts and PBMC was mediated through direct contact and by secreted humoral factors. ICAM-1 on renal fibroblasts may be involved in the direct cell-to-cell interaction inducing MCP-1 gene expression, which seems to be involved in renal interstitial inflammation.

medical_qa.question: Does progesterone influence vascular function in postmenopausal women?
medical_qa.normalized_answer: Progesterone given without oestrogen does not adversely affect vascular function in postmenopausal women.

medical_qa.question: Does hormone replacement therapy cause a decrease in hepatocyte growth factor in hypertensive women?
medical_qa.normalized_answer: Hormone replacement therapy decreases serum hepatocyte growth factor levels in hypertensive postmenopausal women, independent of blood pressure changes.

medical_qa.question: Does red pepper attenuate cholesteryl ester transfer protein activity and atherosclerosis in cholesterol-fed rabbits?
medical_qa.normalized_answer: Red pepper supplementation reduced CETP activity and atherosclerosis in cholesterol-fed rabbits, as indicated by lower lipid levels and fewer fat droplet deposits.

medical_qa.question: Do anterior hypothalamic lesions inhibit antigen-induced airway eosinophilia in rats?
medical_qa.normalized_answer: AHA lesions inhibit antigen-induced airway eosinophilia in rats, possibly through alteration of sympathetic nervous function.

medical_qa.question: Is cytokeratin 20 a tissue-specific marker for the detection of malignant epithelial cells in the blood of colorectal cancer patients?
medical_qa.normalized_answer: Cytokeratin 20 lacks tissue-specificity and is not suitable as a marker for post-operative surveillance of colorectal cancer patients.

medical_qa.question: Does single dose of acetylsalicylic acid prevent thromboxane release after tourniquet ischemia?
medical_qa.normalized_answer: Pretreatment with a single 100-mg dose of ASA prevents the release of TxB(2) after tourniquet deflation.

medical_qa.question: Does implantation of different malignant human cell lines in an athymic mouse alter success and growth rates of either xenograft?
medical_qa.normalized_answer: Implantation of Raji xenografts and HBT 3477 breast cancer xenografts in the same mouse did not affect xenograft success or growth rates, even when whole-body radiation of 4 Gy was used to promote Raji xenografts.

medical_qa.question: Does calcium supplementation for 1 y reduce body weight or fat mass in young girls?
medical_qa.normalized_answer: Calcium supplementation did not affect body weight, height, or body fat over 1 year in young girls, despite an inverse association between habitual dietary calcium intake and body fat.

medical_qa.question: Are baseline serum levels of mast cell tryptase raised in hemodialysis patients and associated with severity of pruritus?
medical_qa.normalized_answer: Serum mast cell tryptase levels were above 11.4 microg/l in 90.3% of hemodialysis patients, and the intensity of pruritus correlated significantly with tryptase levels.

medical_qa.question: Does nitrous oxide depress electroencephalographic responses to repetitive noxious stimulation in the rat?
medical_qa.normalized_answer: Nitrous oxide at peri-MAC partial pressures prevents EEG activation resulting from noxious electrical stimulation in rats.

medical_qa.question: Does infliximab therapy modify MMP-2 and MMP-9 serum concentrations in chronic arthritis?
medical_qa.normalized_answer: Infliximab therapy did not alter MMP-2 and MMP-9 serum concentrations in patients with chronic arthritis in this study.

medical_qa.question: Is late-life anemia associated with increased risk of recurrent falls?
medical_qa.normalized_answer: Late-life anemia is associated with a 1.91 times greater risk for recurrent falls. Poor physical function partly mediates this association.

medical_qa.question: Is body mass index inversely related to mortality in older people after adjustment for waist circumference?
medical_qa.normalized_answer: Higher BMI values indicate a lower mortality risk after accounting for waist circumference, while higher waist circumference values indicate a higher mortality risk after accounting for BMI.

medical_qa.question: Do dysplastic nodules frequently develop into hepatocellular carcinoma in patients with chronic viral hepatitis and cirrhosis?
medical_qa.normalized_answer: High-grade dysplastic nodules have a higher risk of developing into hepatocellular carcinoma compared to low-grade dysplastic nodules and regenerative nodules in patients with chronic viral hepatitis and cirrhosis.

medical_qa.question: Is a positive orientation toward early motherhood associated with unintended pregnancy among New Orleans youth?
medical_qa.normalized_answer: Young women's positive orientation toward early motherhood is independently associated with an increased likelihood of experiencing unintended pregnancies.

medical_qa.question: Does short-term soy and probiotic supplementation markedly affect concentrations of reproductive hormones in postmenopausal women with and without histories of breast cancer?
medical_qa.normalized_answer: Short-term consumption of isoflavone-containing soy protein and probiotic capsules did not significantly alter reproductive hormone concentrations in postmenopausal women with or without histories of breast cancer.

medical_qa.question: Do polyphenol contents in grape-seed extracts correlate with antipica effects in cisplatin-treated rats?
medical_qa.normalized_answer: The study demonstrated that different polyphenol contents in grape-seed extracts correlated with varying antipica effects in cisplatin-treated rats, highlighting the importance of standardization in herbal product preparations.

medical_qa.question: Are distal adenomatous polyps rare in patients with inflammatory bowel disease?
medical_qa.normalized_answer: Distal adenomatous polyps are rare in patients aged 55-64 years with IBD compared with a control population.

medical_qa.question: Does selenomethionine prevent degeneration induced by overexpression of wild-type human alpha-synuclein during differentiation of neuroblastoma cells?
medical_qa.normalized_answer: Selenomethionine reduced degenerative changes induced by overexpression of wild-type human alpha-synuclein during neuroblastoma cell differentiation, suggesting a potential involvement of increased oxidative stress.

medical_qa.question: Does pituitary tumor-transforming gene regulate multiple downstream angiogenic genes in thyroid cancer?
medical_qa.normalized_answer: ID3 and TSP-1 are identified as downstream targets of PTTG in thyroid cancer, suggesting PTTG may influence angiogenesis by regulating various genes with pro- and antiangiogenic properties.

medical_qa.question: Are low sex hormone-binding globulin , total testosterone , and symptomatic androgen deficiency associated with development of the metabolic syndrome in nonobese men?
medical_qa.normalized_answer: Low serum SHBG, low total testosterone, and clinical AD are associated with increased risk of developing MetS over time, particularly in nonoverweight, middle-aged men (BMI, <25).

medical_qa.question: Is endourological management better in early-onset ureteral stenosis in kidney transplantation?
medical_qa.normalized_answer: Balloon dilatation may be considered the definitive procedure for treatment of ureteral stenosis in selected cases.

medical_qa.question: Does hemoperfusion with an immobilized polymyxin B column reduce the blood level of neutrophil elastase?
medical_qa.normalized_answer: Hemoperfusion with an immobilized polymyxin B column reduces circulating neutrophil elastase levels.

medical_qa.question: Do HIV-1-specific CD4+ T-cell responses show significant viral epitope variation in individuals with persistent plasma viremia?
medical_qa.normalized_answer: In chronically infected viremic individuals, CD4 T-cell responses were directed against epitope sequences present in the predominant strain of circulating plasma HIV-1, indicating that evasion from CD4 T-cell responses is not common in vivo.

medical_qa.question: Do chitosan-g-PEG/DNA complexes deliver gene to the rat liver via intrabiliary and intraportal infusions?
medical_qa.normalized_answer: Chitosan-g-PEG/DNA complexes showed higher gene expression in the liver compared to chitosan/DNA complexes after intrabiliary infusion and significant transgene expression after intraportal infusion in rats.

medical_qa.question: Does prevalence and correlate of ADHD symptoms in the national health interview survey?
medical_qa.normalized_answer: ADHD symptoms vary by race, ethnicity, gender, and age and are associated with other emotional and behavioral difficulties. Overdiagnosis and underdiagnosis of ADHD may be present in the U.S. population of 4- to 17-year-olds.

medical_qa.question: Is routine follow-up imaging unnecessary in the management of blunt hepatic injury?
medical_qa.normalized_answer: Routine in-hospital follow-up scans are not indicated as part of the nonoperative management of blunt liver injuries. Follow-up scans are indicated for patients who develop signs or symptoms suggestive of hepatic abnormality.

medical_qa.question: Does rapid warfarin reversal in anticoagulated patients with traumatic intracranial hemorrhage reduce hemorrhage progression and mortality?
medical_qa.normalized_answer: Rapid confirmation of intracranial hemorrhage with head CT scan and prompt reversal of warfarin anticoagulation with fresh frozen plasma decreases hemorrhage progression and reduces mortality.

medical_qa.question: Does energy substrate-supplemented resuscitation affect brain monocarboxylate transporter levels and gliosis in a rat model of hemorrhagic shock?
medical_qa.normalized_answer: Resuscitation with monocarboxylate (MC)-based fluids in hemorrhagic shock increased brain MCT1 levels and activated astrocytes, potentially providing neurons with essential energy substrates.

medical_qa.question: Does mitomycin C inhibit recurrent Avellino dystrophy after phototherapeutic keratectomy?
medical_qa.normalized_answer: Intraoperative use of topical 0.02% MMC with PTK may prevent or delay recurrence of ACD for at least 1 year.

medical_qa.question: Does early heart rate recovery after exercise predict mortality in patients with chronic heart failure?
medical_qa.normalized_answer: Early heart rate recovery is an independent prognostic risk indicator in chronic heart failure patients.

medical_qa.question: Does insulin sensitivity independently influence brachial-ankle pulse-wave velocity in non-diabetic subjects?
medical_qa.normalized_answer: Insulin resistance is independently associated with PWV in non-diabetic subjects.

medical_qa.question: Is adenoidectomy and/or tonsillectomy in childhood associated with atopic disease later in life?
medical_qa.normalized_answer: There is no association between adenoidectomy and/or tonsillectomy in childhood and the incidence of atopic disease in young adults.

medical_qa.question: Does measurement of serum levels of macrophage inhibitory cytokine 1 combined with prostate-specific antigen improve prostate cancer diagnosis?
medical_qa.normalized_answer: Serum MIC-1 is an independent marker of the presence of PCa and tumors with a Gleason sum of > or =7, increasing diagnostic specificity and potentially aiding in PCa management.

medical_qa.question: Is overexpression of peptidyl-prolyl isomerase-like 1 associated with the growth of colon cancer cells?
medical_qa.normalized_answer: Yes, overexpression of peptidyl-prolyl isomerase-like 1 (PPIL1) is associated with the growth of colon cancer cells.

medical_qa.question: Does meta-analysis of the p53 mutation database for mutant p53 biological activity reveal a methodologic bias in mutation detection?
medical_qa.normalized_answer: Functional analysis is crucial to accurately interpret genetic variations in the p53 mutation database and prevent erroneous conclusions. Quality of p53 databases is vital to avoid biased analysis. Access to functional data on the new p53 websites can help identify potential artifactual data.

medical_qa.question: Is vascular endothelial growth factor messenger RNA expression level preserved in liver metastases compared with corresponding primary colorectal cancer?
medical_qa.normalized_answer: VEGF mRNA levels in primary colorectal cancer and corresponding liver metastases showed no significant difference, with a strong correlation between the two. Patients with multiple liver metastatic tumors had higher VEGF mRNA levels compared to those with solitary tumors.

medical_qa.question: Are vascular endothelial growth factor plasma levels significantly elevated in patients with cerebral arteriovenous malformations?
medical_qa.normalized_answer: VEGF plasma concentrations were significantly higher in patients with cerebral AVMs compared to healthy controls, suggesting a potential role in the pathogenesis of cerebral AVMs.

medical_qa.question: Is gH effect on enzyme activity of 11betaHSD in abdominal obesity dependent on treatment duration?
medical_qa.normalized_answer: Short- and long-term GH treatment has different effects on 11betaHSD1 and 11betaHSD2 activity. Long-term metabolic effects of GH are not mediated through its action on 11betaHSD.

medical_qa.question: Are plasma osteoprotegerin levels associated with glycaemic status, systolic blood pressure, kidney function, and cardiovascular morbidity in type 1 diabetic patients?
medical_qa.normalized_answer: OPG is associated with glycaemic control and CVD in patients with type 1 diabetes.

medical_qa.question: Is empiric use of ampicillin and cefotaxime, compared with ampicillin and gentamicin, for neonates at risk for sepsis associated with an increased risk of neonatal death?
medical_qa.normalized_answer: The concurrent use of cefotaxime with ampicillin in neonates is associated with a higher risk of death compared to using gentamicin alongside ampicillin.

medical_qa.question: Do telomerase-specific T-cells kill pancreatic tumor cells in vitro and in vivo?
medical_qa.normalized_answer: Antigen-specific T-cells with cytotoxic activity were generated and expanded successfully. In vitro, these cells showed significant cytotoxic activity against telomerase-positive pancreatic carcinoma cells. In vivo, adoptive cell transfer with murine antigen-specific T-cells delayed disease progression in tumor-bearing mice.

medical_qa.question: Does activation of receptor for advanced glycation end products in osteoarthritis lead to increased stimulation of chondrocytes and synoviocytes?
medical_qa.normalized_answer: Activation of receptor for advanced glycation end products in osteoarthritis leads to increased catabolic activity in chondrocytes and fibroblast-like synoviocytes, contributing to cartilage degradation.

medical_qa.question: Is lymphopenia at presentation associated with increased risk of infections in patients with systemic lupus erythematosus?
medical_qa.normalized_answer: Lymphopenia at presentation was independently associated with an increased risk for major infections in Chinese patients with early-stage systemic lupus erythematosus.

medical_qa.question: Do insulin resistance/compensatory hyperinsulinemia predict carotid intimal medial thickness in patients with essential hypertension?
medical_qa.normalized_answer: Fasting insulin independently predicts the thickness of the intima-media layer in patients with essential hypertension, suggesting a link between insulin resistance/hyperinsulinemia and increased carotid intimal medial thickness.

medical_qa.question: Are plasma sitosterol elevations associated with an increased incidence of coronary events in men : results of a nested case-control analysis of the Prospective Cardiovascular Münster ( PROCAM ) study?
medical_qa.normalized_answer: Elevations in sitosterol concentrations and the sitosterol/cholesterol ratio are associated with an increased occurrence of major coronary events in men at high global risk of coronary heart disease.

medical_qa.question: Do polyunsaturated fatty acids of marine origin induce adiponectin in mice fed a high-fat diet?
medical_qa.normalized_answer: Intake of diets rich in EPA and DHA leads to elevated systemic concentrations of adiponectin, largely independent of food intake or adiposity.

medical_qa.question: Does dietary supplementation of carbonate promote spontaneous tumorigenesis in a rat gastric stump model?
medical_qa.normalized_answer: Dietary supplementation of carbonate promoted tumorigenesis in a rat gastric stump model, suggesting a significant role of carbonate in inducing gastric carcinoma.

medical_qa.question: Does reverse gastric pacing reduce food intake without inducing symptoms in dogs?
medical_qa.normalized_answer: Reverse gastric pacing (RGP) reduces food intake in dogs without inducing symptoms. Moderate RGP did not cause significant symptoms and showed potential for obesity therapy.

medical_qa.question: Do coeliac children on a gluten-free diet with or without oats display equal anti-avenin antibody titres?
medical_qa.normalized_answer: Children with coeliac disease on a gluten-free diet with or without oats showed equal levels of anti-avenin antibodies, suggesting that oats do not trigger a humoral immune response in these patients.

medical_qa.question: Is spirometry related to perinatal outcomes in pregnant women with asthma?
medical_qa.normalized_answer: Lower pulmonary function during pregnancy is associated with increased gestational hypertension and prematurity in women with asthma.

medical_qa.question: Is older colder : temperature range and variation in older people?
medical_qa.normalized_answer: Older subjects have mean oral body temperatures lower than 98.6 degrees F, with few reaching this temperature. Nursing home residents show lower temperatures in the oldest individuals and no diurnal rise in body temperature.

medical_qa.question: Is house dust mite sensitivity a factor in chronic urticaria?
medical_qa.normalized_answer: House dust mite sensitivity may be associated with chronic urticaria based on the study findings.

medical_qa.question: Is collagen degradation by interleukin-1beta-stimulated gingival fibroblasts accompanied by release and activation of multiple matrix metalloproteinases and cysteine proteinases?
medical_qa.normalized_answer: Fibroblast MMP-1 was likely responsible for collagen dissolution in the culture model, with cathepsin B potentially involved in an activation pathway. Various proteinases contribute to extracellular matrix destruction in inflamed gingival tissue through proteolytic cascades.

medical_qa.question: Do increase of MMP-13 expression in multi-stage oral carcinogenesis and epigallocatechin-3-gallate suppress MMP-13 expression?
medical_qa.normalized_answer: Increase of MMP-13 expression is observed in multi-stage oral carcinogenesis. Treatment with epigallocatechin-3-gallate (EGCG) suppresses the expression and activity of MMP-13.

medical_qa.question: Does intensive continuing medical education course training on simulators result in proficiency for laparoscopic suturing?
medical_qa.normalized_answer: A 4-hour laparoscopic suturing CME course with active instruction from proctors allowed 72% of participants to achieve proficiency, showing significant improvement in performance.

medical_qa.question: Do abdominal positron-emission tomography lesions with increased standardized uptake values correlate with intraoperative findings?
medical_qa.normalized_answer: Patients with potentially resectable disease by PET scan but decreased FDG uptake should undergo laparoscopic evaluation before performing laparotomy.

medical_qa.question: Does chlorthalidone improve endothelial-mediated vascular responses in hypertension complicated by nondiabetic metabolic syndrome?
medical_qa.normalized_answer: Chlorthalidone improved endothelial function, reversed abnormal arteriolar structure, and slowed albumin permeation in hypertensive patients with nondiabetic metabolic syndrome.

medical_qa.question: Does heparin therapy lead to platelet activation and prolongation of PFA-100 closure time?
medical_qa.normalized_answer: Unfractionated heparin leads to direct platelet activation and increases platelet aggregation in vitro. It causes prolongation of the collagen/adenosine diphosphate closure time in PFA-100 testing.

medical_qa.question: Does p42/44 MAPK mediate synthesis of fractalkine by mesangial cells stimulated by connective tissue growth factor?
medical_qa.normalized_answer: The phosphorylation of p42/44 MAPK was associated with CTGF-induced secretion of FLK by mesangial cells.

medical_qa.question: Does analysis of neovascularization of PEGT/PBT-copolymer dermis substitute in balb/c-mice?
medical_qa.normalized_answer: The pore size structure of PEGT/PBT-block-copolymer matrices influences neovascularization, with faster ingrowth of vascular tissue observed in matrices with pore sizes of 75-212 and 250-300 microm.

medical_qa.question: Does weight loss reduce adipose tissue cathepsin S and its circulating levels in morbidly obese women?
medical_qa.normalized_answer: Weight loss decreased circulating CTSS levels, CTSS enzymatic activity, and adipose tissue CTSS content in morbidly obese women.

medical_qa.question: Do common polymorphisms of the growth hormone ( GH ) receptor correlate with the growth response to exogenous recombinant human GH in GH-deficient children?
medical_qa.normalized_answer: Common GHR polymorphisms, alone or in combination, do not seem to impact the growth response to rhGH in GH-deficient children.

medical_qa.question: Is simulation-based training superior to problem-based learning for the acquisition of critical assessment and management skills?
medical_qa.normalized_answer: Simulation-based learning was superior to problem-based learning for fourth-year medical students in acquiring critical assessment and management skills.

medical_qa.question: Does cXCL12 attract CXCR4+ human metastatic neuroblastoma cells : clinical implications?
medical_qa.normalized_answer: CXCR4 expressed in human metastatic neuroblastoma cells is not functional, indicating that CXCR4 antagonists may not be effective in preventing neuroblastoma metastasis.

medical_qa.question: Do in chronic idiopathic urticaria autoantibodies against Fc epsilonRII/CD23 induce histamine release via eosinophil activation?
medical_qa.normalized_answer: Patients with chronic idiopathic urticaria have autoantibodies against CD23, and eosinophils play a role in the disease by releasing major basic protein upon engagement of the low-affinity IgE receptor by these autoantibodies.

medical_qa.question: Are clinical effects of probiotics associated with increased interferon-gamma responses in very young children with atopic dermatitis?
medical_qa.normalized_answer: Probiotic treatment in young children with atopic dermatitis led to improved disease severity linked to increased Th1 IFN-gamma responses and changes in responses to skin and gut flora. These effects persisted even after stopping the supplementation. The inconsistent effects on allergen-specific responses suggest probiotics may act through different pathways.

medical_qa.question: Is tumor necrosis factor-alpha gene G-308A polymorphism a risk factor for the development of membranous glomerulonephritis?
medical_qa.normalized_answer: The study indicates that TNF-alpha gene G-308A polymorphism may be associated with membranous glomerulonephritis development.

medical_qa.question: Is methionine-induced elevation of plasma homocysteine concentration associated with an increase of plasma cholesterol in adult rats?
medical_qa.normalized_answer: Dietary methionine contributes to increased circulating homocysteine levels which correlate positively with plasma cholesterol concentration in adult rats.

medical_qa.question: Do erythrocyte concentrations of metabolites or cumulative doses of 6-mercaptopurine and methotrexate predict liver changes in children treated for acute lymphoblastic leukemia?
medical_qa.normalized_answer: Erythrocyte levels of metabolites or cumulative doses of 6MP and MTX do not predict histological liver disease in children treated for ALL.

medical_qa.question: Is intranasal sufentanil effective for postoperative analgesia in adults?
medical_qa.normalized_answer: Intranasal sufentanil at a dose of 0.050 microg x kg(-1) /puff provided effective postoperative analgesia within one hour, with efficacy seen after 20 minutes. This study supports intranasal sufentanil as an effective option for immediate postoperative pain relief in adults.

medical_qa.question: Do a single dose of fentanyl and midazolam prior to Cesarean section have no adverse neonatal effects?
medical_qa.normalized_answer: Maternal analgesia and sedation with fentanyl and midazolam before spinal anesthesia did not show adverse neonatal effects.

medical_qa.question: Is when a leak unavoidable , preoxygenation is equally ineffective with vital capacity or tidal volume breathing?
medical_qa.normalized_answer: Preoxygenation with tidal volume breathing for three minutes is more effective than with four vital capacity breaths. When a small leak is present, the oxygen fraction decreases significantly with both methods to around 60%.

medical_qa.question: Is a functional promotor polymorphism of TNF-alpha associated with primary gastric B-Cell lymphoma?
medical_qa.normalized_answer: The study found that carriers of the TNF-857 T allele had an increased risk of developing low-grade and high-grade gastric B-cell lymphoma compared to healthy controls and H. pylori-infected patients. However, no associations were found between other TNF-alpha gene polymorphisms and disease progression.

medical_qa.question: Is activation of stat3 in primary tumors from high-risk breast cancer patients associated with elevated levels of activated SRC and survivin expression?
medical_qa.normalized_answer: Elevated levels of activated pY-Stat3 and pY-Src were significantly higher in invasive carcinoma compared to nonneoplastic tissue. In tumors, elevated pY-Stat3 levels correlated with pY-Src and Survivin expression.

medical_qa.question: Do soluble donor DNA concentrations in recipient serum correlate with pancreas-kidney rejection?
medical_qa.normalized_answer: Quantification of donor-specific genomic DNA in recipient serum showed higher concentrations in pancreas-kidney transplant recipients who experienced allograft rejection compared to those who did not, suggesting a potential marker for rejection.

medical_qa.question: Does surgery by consultant gynecologic oncologists improve survival in patients with ovarian carcinoma?
medical_qa.normalized_answer: Surgery by gynecologic oncologists for ovarian carcinoma patients improved survival rates compared to general gynecologists.

medical_qa.question: Does prodromal angina reduce infarcted mass less in interventionally reperfused than in thrombolysed myocardial infarction?
medical_qa.normalized_answer: Preinfarction angina under 48 hours significantly reduces infarcted mass in thrombolysed patients, but not in the interventional group. However, PIA reduced arrhythmic end-point in interventional setting.

medical_qa.question: Does the WAVE2 complex regulate actin cytoskeletal reorganization and CRAC-mediated calcium entry during T cell activation?
medical_qa.normalized_answer: WAVE2 is involved in actin reorganization at the immune synapse and regulates calcium entry in T cells, linking intracellular calcium store depletion to CRAC channel activation.

medical_qa.question: Does treatment with Met-RANTES decrease bacterial translocation in experimental colitis?
medical_qa.normalized_answer: Met-RANTES treatment resulted in significant decreases in colonic damage and bacterial translocation in experimental colitis.

medical_qa.question: Is rubella virus associated with Fuchs heterochromic iridocyclitis?
medical_qa.normalized_answer: Rubella virus is associated with Fuchs heterochromic iridocyclitis, while HSV, VZV, and T gondii are not.

medical_qa.question: Is an absent pulse sensitive for the early detection of peripheral arterial disease?
medical_qa.normalized_answer: Pulse palpation is not sensitive for the detection of peripheral arterial disease compared to ankle-brachial index (ABI).

medical_qa.question: Does polymorphism of the glycoprotein Ia and IIIa in the group of women in childbirth correlate with an increased risk of developing thrombosis?
medical_qa.normalized_answer: The study did not find a causative relationship between platelets GP IIIa/GP Ia mutations and venous system thrombosis in women in labor. Presence of pro-thrombotic mutations of platelets glycoprotein in this group may not represent an increased risk of thrombosis.

medical_qa.question: Are specific haplotypes of the CALPAIN-5 gene associated with polycystic ovary syndrome?
medical_qa.normalized_answer: The study suggests a role of CAPN5 gene in PCOS susceptibility and identifies specific haplotypes associated with phenotypic differences in PCOS patients.

medical_qa.question: Is chronic infarct-related artery occlusion associated with a reduction in capillary density? Effects on infarct healing?
medical_qa.normalized_answer: Chronic total infarct-related artery occlusion is associated with a significant reduction in capillary density in the infarcted area.

medical_qa.question: Does ciliary neurotrophic factor restore gallbladder contractility in leptin-resistant obese diabetic mice?
medical_qa.normalized_answer: Ciliary neurotrophic factor (CNTF) improves weight loss, diabetes, and gallbladder motility in obese mice, but decreases gallbladder contraction in lean mice. CNTF may enhance gallbladder contractility in leptin-resistant obese diabetic mice.

medical_qa.question: Do fFT analysis of the X-ray tube voltage waveforms of high-frequency generators for radiographic systems?
medical_qa.normalized_answer: FFT analysis of high-frequency X-ray generators' voltage waveforms can objectively compare and detect changes in the waveform, aiding in quality assurance.

medical_qa.question: Does Crohn's disease run a more aggressive course in young Asian patients?
medical_qa.normalized_answer: Young Crohn's disease patients in an Asian population showed a more aggressive clinical course compared to older patients.

medical_qa.question: Do effect of patient load on trauma outcomes in a Level I trauma center?
medical_qa.normalized_answer: Patient outcomes were not compromised during high-patient-load periods, at night, or on weekends at this Level I trauma center.

medical_qa.question: Does hypotension increase mortality in brain-injured patients more than it does in non-brain-injured Patients?
medical_qa.normalized_answer: Hypotension is an independent risk factor for mortality. However, it does not increase mortality in TBI patients more than it does for non-TBI patients.

medical_qa.question: Do manual vital signs reliably predict need for life-saving interventions in trauma patients?
medical_qa.normalized_answer: In this study, GCS motor and verbal components and radial pulse character without automated monitors effectively predicted the need for life-saving interventions in trauma patients, showing that manual measurements could be used for triage.

medical_qa.question: Does aprotinin decrease reperfusion injury and allograft dysfunction in clinical lung transplantation?
medical_qa.normalized_answer: The use of aprotinin in perioperative management during lung transplantation decreased the incidence of post-transplant ischemia-reperfusion injury significantly.

medical_qa.question: Is lymphovascular invasion associated with poor survival in gastric cancer : an application of gene-expression and tissue array techniques?
medical_qa.normalized_answer: LVI was an independent predictor of survival in gastric cancer. COX-2 expression may facilitate tumor invasion through MMP-2 and MMP-9 activation. OPHN1 and RPN II were differentially expressed in gastric cancers with LVI.

medical_qa.question: Are ghrelin levels increased in alcoholism?
medical_qa.normalized_answer: Ghrelin levels are elevated in alcoholism and increase during alcohol withdrawal, but are not associated with alcohol craving.

medical_qa.question: Does human macroprolactin display low biological activity via its homologous receptor in a new sensitive bioassay?
medical_qa.normalized_answer: The study suggests that the biological activity of macroprolactin towards the rat receptor may not be relevant as it is not observed in the human PRL receptor-mediated assay, consistent with the lack of bioactivity in vivo.

medical_qa.question: Does thyrotropin stimulate the generation of inositol 1,4,5-trisphosphate in human thyroid cells?
medical_qa.normalized_answer: Thyrotropin stimulates the generation of inositol 1,4,5-trisphosphate and its inositol phosphate metabolites in human thyroid cells, but not in FRTL-5 cells. The effect in human cells is mediated through cAMP and the phospholipase C cascade.

medical_qa.question: Does the effect of telephone appointment-reminder call on outpatient absenteeism in a pulmonary function laboratory?
medical_qa.normalized_answer: Telephone appointment-reminder calls reduce outpatient-appointment absenteeism at a hospital-based pulmonary function laboratory. There was no significant difference in absenteeism between reminders via direct conversation or leaving a message on an answering machine.

medical_qa.question: Does residual air in the venous cannula increase cerebral embolization at the onset of cardiopulmonary bypass?
medical_qa.normalized_answer: Air in the venous cannula can lead to high-intensity transient signals (HITS) in the middle cerebral arteries (MCA), affecting cerebral embolization during cardiopulmonary bypass (CPB). Minimizing the volume of air in the venous cannula after right atrium (RA) cannulation can help reduce this risk.

medical_qa.question: Does indexed effective orifice area after mechanical aortic valve replacement affect left ventricular mass regression in elderly?
medical_qa.normalized_answer: Patient-prosthesis mismatch does not affect left ventricular mass regression in patients older than 65 with pure aortic stenosis who underwent mechanical aortic valve replacement.

medical_qa.question: Does adjustment of antibiotic treatment according to the results of blood cultures lead to decreased antibiotic use and costs?
medical_qa.normalized_answer: Adjustment of antibiotic therapy based on blood culture results led to a reduction in the number of antibiotics used and a decrease in antibiotic costs.

medical_qa.question: Do glycosaminoglycans inhibit the antibacterial activity of LL-37 in biological fluids?
medical_qa.normalized_answer: Glycosaminoglycan-rich biological fluids inhibit the antibacterial effects of LL-37. Polycations that bind to glycosaminoglycans increase the antibacterial activities of endogenous antimicrobial peptides in glycosaminoglycan-containing biological fluids.

medical_qa.question: Does production of a novel class of polyreactive pathogenic autoantibodies in BXD2 mice cause glomerulonephritis and arthritis?
medical_qa.normalized_answer: Polyreactive autoantibodies in BXD2 mice may induce erosive arthritis or glomerulonephritis through direct pathogenic mechanisms or immune complex deposition.

medical_qa.question: Do audio spectrum and sound pressure levels vary between pulse oximeters?
medical_qa.normalized_answer: There is considerable variance in the sound pressure and audio spectrum of commercially-available pulse oximeters.

medical_qa.question: Does acute weight loss followed by an aggressive nutritional recovery strategy have little impact on on-water rowing performance?
medical_qa.normalized_answer: Acute weight loss of up to 4% over 24 hours, combined with aggressive nutritional recovery strategies, has minimal impact on on-water rowing performance.

medical_qa.question: Are oxidized-LDL levels changed during short-term serum glucose variations and lowered with statin treatment in early Type 2 diabetes : a study of endothelial function and microalbuminuria?
medical_qa.normalized_answer: In early obese Type 2 diabetic patients, serum ox-LDL levels are influenced by short-term serum glucose variations and lowered with cerivastatin therapy. During cerivastatin treatment, improved flow-mediated endothelium-dependent dilation was associated with decrements in circulating ox-LDL levels and the hyperinsulinaemia-induced urinary albumin excretion was blunted.

medical_qa.question: Is clinically apparent atherosclerotic disease in diabetes associated with an increase in platelet microparticle levels?
medical_qa.normalized_answer: Patients with Type 2 diabetes and clinically apparent atherosclerotic disease had the highest levels of platelet microparticles (PMPs) and soluble plasma P-selectin (sPsel).

medical_qa.question: Does Glasgow Aneurysm Score predict survival after endovascular stenting of abdominal aortic aneurysm in patients from the EUROSTAR registry?
medical_qa.normalized_answer: The Glasgow Aneurysm Score (GAS) effectively predicts outcomes after endovascular repair of abdominal aortic aneurysms, as demonstrated in patients from the EUROSTAR registry.

medical_qa.question: Does transesophageal echocardiography disclose unexpected cardiac sources of embolus in stroke patients aged more than 45 years?
medical_qa.normalized_answer: Transesophageal echocardiography can reveal cardiac sources of embolism in stroke patients aged over 45 years, highlighting the importance of assessing atherogenic and cardioembolic causes in this population.

medical_qa.question: Do academic mothers have a pronounced seasonal variation in their offspring sex ratio?
medical_qa.normalized_answer: Academic mothers show a significant seasonal variation in the sex ratio of their offspring, with an increase during spring and a decrease during summer, while non-academic mothers have a less pronounced and non-significant trend.

medical_qa.question: Does acetaldehyde inhibit the formation of retinoic acid from retinal in the rat esophagus?
medical_qa.normalized_answer: Acetaldehyde inhibits the formation of retinoic acid from retinal in the rat esophagus, potentially explaining the higher incidence of esophageal cancer in alcoholics.

medical_qa.question: Is routine once-weekly darbepoetin alfa administration cost-effective in lung cancer patients with chemotherapy-induced anemia : a Markov analysis?
medical_qa.normalized_answer: Routine use of darbepoetin alfa seems to be cost-effective in lung cancer patients receiving chemotherapy.

medical_qa.question: Does passive resistance increase differentially in various jaw displacement directions?
medical_qa.normalized_answer: Stiffness of jaw displacement is higher in the protrusive direction compared to the vertical and lateral directions.

medical_qa.question: Is empiric acyclovir infrequently initiated in the emergency department to patients ultimately diagnosed with encephalitis?
medical_qa.normalized_answer: Empiric acyclovir was not frequently initiated in the emergency department for patients ultimately diagnosed with encephalitis.

medical_qa.question: Is oxidant release dramatically increased by elevated glucose concentrations in neutrophils from pregnant women?
medical_qa.normalized_answer: Elevated glucose levels enhance HMS activity and oxidant production in cells from pregnant women.

medical_qa.question: Does riboflavin lower homocysteine in individuals homozygous for the MTHFR 677C- > T polymorphism?
medical_qa.normalized_answer: Homocysteine levels responded to riboflavin supplementation in individuals with the MTHFR 677 TT genotype, but not in those with CC or CT genotypes, despite preselection for suboptimal riboflavin status.

medical_qa.question: Does cyclooxygenase-1 deficiency in bone marrow cells increase early atherosclerosis in apolipoprotein E- and low-density lipoprotein receptor-null mice?
medical_qa.normalized_answer: COX-1 deficiency in bone marrow-derived cells exacerbates early atherosclerosis in apoE(-/-) and LDLR(-/-) mice despite reduced platelet TX production. Increased COX-2 expression in COX-1(-/-) macrophages is implicated in promoting atherosclerosis.

medical_qa.question: Does inhibition of histone deacetylation block cardiac hypertrophy induced by angiotensin II infusion and aortic banding?
medical_qa.normalized_answer: HDAC inhibitors, including a class I HDAC-selective inhibitor, were found to reduce cardiac hypertrophy induced by angiotensin II infusion and aortic banding in mice and rats.

medical_qa.question: Does cardiac-specific overexpression of diacylglycerol kinase zeta prevent Gq protein-coupled receptor agonist-induced cardiac hypertrophy in transgenic mice?
medical_qa.normalized_answer: DGKzeta overexpression in the heart prevented GPCR agonist-induced cardiac hypertrophy in transgenic mice without adverse effects.

medical_qa.question: Is plasma triglyceride level an independent predictor of altered left ventricular relaxation?
medical_qa.normalized_answer: Plasma triglyceride levels are significantly associated with impaired left ventricular relaxation, suggesting a potential link to diastolic dysfunction.

medical_qa.question: Does the incorporation of prior genomic information necessarily improve the performance of Bayesian linkage methods?
medical_qa.normalized_answer: Incorporating (correct) prior genomic information is not always helpful. The sex-averaged PPL is recommended as the standard form regardless of sex-specific recombination rates.

medical_qa.question: Are CARD15 single nucleotide polymorphisms 8, 12, and 13 increased in ethnic Danes with sarcoidosis?
medical_qa.normalized_answer: The frequency of CARD15 mutations is not increased in ethnic Danish patients with sarcoidosis, and heterozygosity for such mutations apparently has no influence on the course of disease.

medical_qa.question: Does electroporation-mediated interleukin-10 overexpression in skeletal muscle reduce acute rejection in rat cardiac allografts?
medical_qa.normalized_answer: Electroporation-mediated intramuscular overexpression of hIL-10 reduces acute rejection and improves survival of heterotopic heart allografts in rats.

medical_qa.question: Is removal of the OptEase retrievable vena cava filter feasible after extended time periods because of filter protrusion through the vena cava?
medical_qa.normalized_answer: Removal of the retrievable OptEase VCF may be successfully performed up to 14 days after insertion. Strut protrusion through the VC wall prohibited successful and safe removal at extended time intervals.

medical_qa.question: Do endothelial functions improve with decrease in asymmetric dimethylarginine ( ADMA ) levels after renal transplantation?
medical_qa.normalized_answer: Endothelial functions improve at the beginning of the posttransplantation period with reduction in ADMA levels.

medical_qa.question: Does flow cytometry-based sterility testing work for platelet concentrate?
medical_qa.normalized_answer: Sterility testing of platelet concentrates using flow cytometry is feasible. Incubation for 20-24 hours at 37 degrees C is suggested, with longer periods for slow-growing bacteria.

medical_qa.question: Are elevations of plasma methylarginines in obesity and ageing related to insulin sensitivity and rates of protein turnover?
medical_qa.normalized_answer: Obesity, sex, and ageing impact methylarginines. Elevated methylarginines in obesity and elderly men are associated with increased protein turnover and reduced insulin sensitivity in protein metabolism.

medical_qa.question: Is the value of onsite adequacy assessment of thyroid fine-needle aspirations a function of operator experience?
medical_qa.normalized_answer: Onsite adequacy assessment of thyroid fine-needle aspirations significantly reduces nondiagnostic aspirates. The benefit varies based on the experience of the operator, particularly for ultrasound-guided procedures.

medical_qa.question: Is migraine with aura a risk factor for unprovoked seizures in children?
medical_qa.normalized_answer: Migraine with aura in children is associated with a fourfold increased risk for developing epilepsy, while migraine without aura does not increase the risk.

medical_qa.question: Are substantia nigra tangles related to gait impairment in older persons?
medical_qa.normalized_answer: NFTs in the substantia nigra are associated with gait impairment in older persons with and without dementia.

medical_qa.question: Does beta-carotene supplementation attenuate cardiac remodeling induced by one-month tobacco-smoke exposure in rats?
medical_qa.normalized_answer: Beta-carotene supplementation attenuates cardiac remodeling induced by one-month tobacco-smoke exposure in rats.

medical_qa.question: Is lung transplantation in patients with chronic obstructive pulmonary disease in a national cohort without obvious survival benefit?
medical_qa.normalized_answer: In patients with COPD/emphysema, there was no clear survival benefit from lung transplantation, raising questions about the primary goal of prolonging life with the procedure.

medical_qa.question: Does nitroglycerin reperfusion reduce ischemia-reperfusion injury in non-heart-beating donor lungs?
medical_qa.normalized_answer: Nitroglycerin reperfusion may reduce capillary leak after reperfusion, potentially aiding in safe lung transplantation from non-heart-beating donors.

medical_qa.question: Does spirituality predict outcome independently of expectancy following flower essence self-treatment?
medical_qa.normalized_answer: The study found that spirituality and absorption predicted additional variance in outcomes compared to expectancy measures following flower essence self-treatment.

medical_qa.question: Is combined use of noninvasive tests useful in the initial diagnostic approach to a child with suspected inflammatory bowel disease?
medical_qa.normalized_answer: Using a combination of noninvasive tests in the initial diagnostic approach can help in the evaluation of children with suspected inflammatory bowel disease, potentially avoiding unnecessary invasive procedures and aiding in clinical decision-making.

medical_qa.question: Does metabolic syndrome negatively impact early patency of saphenous vein grafts?
medical_qa.normalized_answer: Metabolic syndrome has a negative impact on saphenous vein graft patency in the short term.

medical_qa.question: Does extracorporeal cardiac shock wave therapy ameliorate myocardial ischemia in patients with severe coronary artery disease?
medical_qa.normalized_answer: Extracorporeal cardiac shock wave therapy improved symptoms, reduced nitroglycerin use, and enhanced myocardial perfusion in patients with end-stage coronary artery disease, with beneficial effects lasting up to 12 months. No procedural complications or adverse effects were reported.

medical_qa.question: Are women with a prior diagnosis of breast cancer at an increased risk for subsequent colorectal cancer?
medical_qa.normalized_answer: Women with a prior diagnosis of breast cancer are not at an increased risk of colorectal cancer.

medical_qa.question: Does patellar taping change the amplitude of electromyographic activity of the vasti in a stair stepping task?
medical_qa.normalized_answer: Patellar taping did not alter the amplitude of vasti electromyographic activity during stair stepping tasks in subjects with or without patellofemoral pain.

medical_qa.question: Are high dose magnesium infusions associated with increased pressor requirements after carotid endarterectomy?
medical_qa.normalized_answer: No significant differences were found in the percentage of patients needing pressor support, duration of support, or amount of phenylephrine required between control and magnesium-treated patients.

medical_qa.question: Do radiographic characteristics fail to predict clinical course after subdural electrode placement?
medical_qa.normalized_answer: Radiographic characteristics such as midline shift and maximal thickness did not effectively differentiate symptomatic and asymptomatic patients with extra-axial collections (EACs) after subdural electrode placement. Total volume calculation showed a statistically significant difference, but no clear volume threshold correlated with clinical outcomes. Therefore, CT scan appearance of EACs has limited predictive value for symptoms and postoperative complications, requiring clinical judgment for management decisions.

medical_qa.question: Does aPOA5 variant Ser19Trp influence a decrease of the total cholesterol in a male 8 year cohort?
medical_qa.normalized_answer: The Ser19 > Trp variant in the APOA5 gene may influence the decrease in total cholesterol levels in males over an 8-year period.

medical_qa.question: Does statistical voxel-wise analysis of ictal SPECT reveal pattern of abnormal perfusion in patients with temporal lobe epilepsy?
medical_qa.normalized_answer: Voxel-wise analysis of ictal brain perfusion SPECT in patients with temporal lobe epilepsy shows perfusional alterations in distant regions, potentially involved in seizure generation and spread.

medical_qa.question: Does deficiency of the 5-hydroxytryptamine transporter gene lead to cardiac fibrosis and valvulopathy in mice?
medical_qa.normalized_answer: 5-HTT deficiency in mice is associated with cardiac fibrosis and valvulopathy, making them a valuable model for studying the mechanisms of 5-HT-induced valvulopathy.

medical_qa.question: Is nuchal cord associated with adverse perinatal outcome?
medical_qa.normalized_answer: Nuchal cord is not associated with adverse perinatal outcome.

medical_qa.question: Is closure of the arteriotomy after carotid endarterectomy : patch type related to intraoperative microemboli and restenosis rate?
medical_qa.normalized_answer: Dacron patches during carotid endarterectomy are associated with more microemboli during clamp releases and wound closure. Dacron patches and primary closure have a higher restenosis rate compared to venous patches.

medical_qa.question: Does xenon provide short-term neuroprotection in neonatal rats when administered after hypoxia-ischemia?
medical_qa.normalized_answer: Xenon administration after hypoxia-ischemia in neonatal rats provides short-term neuroprotection.

medical_qa.question: Are heterozygous mutations in natriuretic peptide receptor-B ( NPR2 ) associated with short stature?
medical_qa.normalized_answer: Heterozygous mutations in NPR2 are associated with short stature.

medical_qa.question: Does acetylsalicylic acid improve lipid-induced insulin resistance in healthy men?
medical_qa.normalized_answer: ASA pretreatment attenuated lipid-induced insulin resistance in healthy men, independent of changes in inflammatory markers.

medical_qa.question: Is acquisition of chemoresistance following discontinuous exposures to cisplatin associated in ovarian carcinoma cells with progressive alteration of FAK , ERK and p38 activation in response to treatment?
medical_qa.normalized_answer: Emergence of chemoresistance was accompanied by progressive loss of ERK and p38 activation and maintenance of FAK activation in response to cisplatin.

medical_qa.question: Do total IgE levels change 1 year after endoscopic sinus surgery in patients with chronic rhinosinusitis?
medical_qa.normalized_answer: Total serum IgE levels did not show any statistically significant change from the preoperative values when measured 1 year postoperatively in patients with chronic rhinosinusitis undergoing endoscopic sinus surgery.

medical_qa.question: Is failure of decidual arteriolar remodeling in the CBA/J x DBA/2 murine model of recurrent pregnancy loss linked to increased expression of tissue inhibitor of metalloproteinase 2 ( TIMP-2 )?
medical_qa.normalized_answer: In the CBA/J x DBA/2 murine model of recurrent pregnancy loss, there is a significant reduction in vascular remodeling compared to normal pregnancies. This reduction is associated with increased expression of tissue inhibitor of metalloproteinase 2 (TIMP-2) protein in the placentas of the affected mice.

medical_qa.question: Is the TRP2 allele of COL9A2 an age-dependent risk factor for the development and severity of intervertebral disc degeneration?
medical_qa.normalized_answer: The Trp2 allele of COL9A2 is a significant age-dependent risk factor for the development and severity of intervertebral disc degeneration, particularly associated with anular tears and disc degeneration in certain age groups.

medical_qa.question: Does severe bacteremia result in a loss of hepatic bacterial clearance?
medical_qa.normalized_answer: Severe bacteremia can lead to a loss of hepatic bacterial clearance, resulting in increased systemic bacteremia and mortality.

medical_qa.question: Does planimetric assessment of anatomic valve area overestimate effective orifice area in bicuspid aortic stenosis?
medical_qa.normalized_answer: Anatomic valve area tends to be overestimated by planimetric assessment in bicuspid aortic stenosis compared to tricuspid aortic stenosis, likely due to jet eccentricity and less pressure recovery.

medical_qa.question: Is sprouty4 , a suppressor of tumor cell motility , down regulated by DNA methylation in human prostate cancer?
medical_qa.normalized_answer: Yes, Sprouty4 expression is down regulated in human prostate cancer by DNA methylation.

medical_qa.question: Does topical becaplermin improve outcomes in work related fingertip injuries?
medical_qa.normalized_answer: Topical becaplermin showed significantly better functional and economic outcomes compared to surgical reconstruction for work-related fingertip injuries.

medical_qa.question: Does deficiency of regulatory B cells increase allergic airway inflammation?
medical_qa.normalized_answer: Regulatory B-1a cells play a role in reducing cytokine production, pulmonary inflammation, and CD4(+) T cell survival during cockroach allergen-induced airway inflammation.

medical_qa.question: Does docetaxel followed by castration improve outcomes in LNCaP prostate cancer-bearing severe combined immunodeficient mice?
medical_qa.normalized_answer: Docetaxel followed by castration showed the most potent antitumor effects in severe combined immunodeficient mice bearing LNCaP prostate tumors.

medical_qa.question: Do the extent of oesophageal acid exposure overlap among the different gastro-oesophageal reflux disease groups?
medical_qa.normalized_answer: There is a high oesophageal acid exposure overlap between patients with non-erosive reflux disease-positive and erosive oesophagitis, Barrett's oesophagus and erosive oesophagitis, as well as Barrett's oesophagus and non-erosive reflux disease-positive patients.

medical_qa.question: Do spinal manipulation force and duration affect vertebral movement and neuromuscular responses?
medical_qa.normalized_answer: Biomechanical and neuromuscular responses in the ovine lumbar spine were influenced by variations in force-time profiles of spinal manipulative thrusts, potentially impacting clinical outcomes.

medical_qa.question: Is balloon kyphoplasty effective in deformity correction of osteoporotic vertebral compression fractures?
medical_qa.normalized_answer: Balloon kyphoplasty is effective in correcting deformities of osteoporotic vertebral compression fractures through dynamic fracture mobility and expansion of the inserted balloon tamp.

medical_qa.question: Is t-cell recognition of a prostate specific antigen sufficient to induce prostate tissue destruction?
medical_qa.normalized_answer: T lymphocytes specific for a prostate antigen can induce inflammatory infiltration of prostatic tissue but do not cause pathological prostate injury.

medical_qa.question: Are genetic polymorphisms of CD14, toll-like receptor 4, and caspase-recruitment domain 15 associated with necrotizing enterocolitis in very low birth weight infants?
medical_qa.normalized_answer: Carrier state of the tested CD14, TLR4, and CARD15 SNPs is not associated with NEC risk in VLBW infants.

medical_qa.question: Is spinal cord stimulation cost-effective for non-surgical management of critical limb ischaemia?
medical_qa.normalized_answer: Spinal cord stimulation (SCS) for critical limb ischaemia (CLI) is more expensive than best medical treatment, with no long-term benefits observed, making it less cost-effective.

medical_qa.question: Does deep sedation occur frequently during elective endoscopy with meperidine and midazolam?
medical_qa.normalized_answer: Deep sedation occurs frequently during elective endoscopy with meperidine and midazolam, with ERCP and EUS being independent risk factors for its occurrence.

medical_qa.question: Does overexpression of STAT-1 by adenoviral gene transfer inhibit hepatitis B virus replication?
medical_qa.normalized_answer: Overexpression of STAT-1 alone is not sufficient to enhance the biological response of interferon as an antiviral agent.

medical_qa.question: Does gleason scoring vary among pathologists and this affects clinical risk in patients with prostate cancer?
medical_qa.normalized_answer: Gleason scoring varies among pathologists, with 19% of cases having their grading changed, affecting clinical risk and treatment strategy, usually worsening prognosis.

medical_qa.question: Does addition of platelet transfusions to corticosteroids increase the recovery of severe HELLP syndrome?
medical_qa.normalized_answer: Platelet transfusions added to corticosteroids did not improve recovery in patients with true HELLP syndrome. Dexamethasone alone led to faster platelet count normalization compared to dexamethasone plus platelet transfusion.

medical_qa.question: Are flow-dependent changes in Doppler-derived aortic valve effective orifice area real and not due to artifact?
medical_qa.normalized_answer: The flow-dependent changes in Doppler-derived aortic valve effective orifice area are real and not due to artifact, attributed to unsteady effects at low flow rates and changes in valve leaflet opening.

medical_qa.question: Does cryopreservation of hematopoietic progenitor cells from apheresis at high cell concentrations impair the hematopoietic recovery after transplantation?
medical_qa.normalized_answer: Cryopreserving hematopoietic progenitor cells from apheresis at high cell concentrations does not negatively affect hematopoietic recovery after transplantation.

medical_qa.question: Does desensitization to strong vestibular stimuli improve tolerance to simulated aircraft motion?
medical_qa.normalized_answer: Desensitization to one provocative motion may be transferred to a less severe motion stimulus, potentially useful in refining desensitization programs for aircrew.

medical_qa.question: Is h244R VSX1 associated with selective cone ON bipolar cell dysfunction and macular degeneration in a PPCD family?
medical_qa.normalized_answer: The H244R variant in the VSX1 gene segregated with corneal and macular disease phenotypes in the PPCD family, showing selective cone ON bipolar cell dysfunction.

medical_qa.question: Are globally , CYP1B1 mutations in primary congenital glaucoma strongly structured by geographic and haplotype backgrounds?
medical_qa.normalized_answer: The association of specific haplotypes with predominant CYP1B1 mutations in primary congenital glaucoma shows geographical clustering, likely due to founder effects.

medical_qa.question: Is pancreatic cancer cells invasiveness mainly affected by interleukin-1beta not by transforming growth factor-beta1?
medical_qa.normalized_answer: IL-1beta enhances the invasive capacity of pancreatic cancer cells, whereas TGF-beta1 has paradoxical effects on pancreatic cancer cells.

medical_qa.question: Is evolution of the renal function a better predictor of long-term survival than serum creatinine?
medical_qa.normalized_answer: Renal function changes at 3 months and throughout the evolution were better predictors of graft failure than a single serum creatinine value.

medical_qa.question: Does Lysophosphatidic acid activate L-arginine/nitric oxide pathway of platelets in rats?
medical_qa.normalized_answer: Lysophosphatidic acid increased NO release by enhancing L-arginine uptake and NOS activities, up-regulating L-arginine/NOS/NO pathway in platelets of rats.

medical_qa.question: Is Cell-cycle negative regulatory gene ANA over-expressed in the brain tissues of patients with Down syndrome?
medical_qa.normalized_answer: ANA, a cell-cycle negative regulatory gene, was over-expressed dramatically in the cortex but not in the cerebellum of DS.

medical_qa.question: Is young age a risk factor for HIV among female sex workers -- an experience from India?
medical_qa.normalized_answer: Younger age (< or =20 years) was found to be a significant risk factor for HIV infection among female sex workers in India, with a higher prevalence compared to older age groups.

medical_qa.question: Does anti-tumor necrosis factor therapy increase synovial osteoprotegerin expression in rheumatoid arthritis?
medical_qa.normalized_answer: Therapy with TNF antagonists in RA modulates the OPG/RANKL system, potentially explaining the retardation of radiographic damage observed following anti-TNF therapy.

medical_qa.question: Does postmastectomy radiotherapy reduce locoregional recurrence in elderly women with high-risk breast cancer?
medical_qa.normalized_answer: In elderly women aged 70 years or over with high-risk breast cancer, postmastectomy radiotherapy significantly reduces locoregional recurrence compared to no radiotherapy.

medical_qa.question: Does cyclosporine suppress cell growth and collagen production in hepatic stellate cells?
medical_qa.normalized_answer: Cyclosporine suppresses cell growth and collagen production in hepatic stellate cells, indicating a potential antifibrogenic effect.

medical_qa.question: Are increased plasma markers of oxidative stress associated with coronary heart disease in males with diabetes mellitus and with 10-year risk in a prospective sample of males?
medical_qa.normalized_answer: Baseline plasma measures of oxidative stress are associated with coronary heart disease risk in males with diabetes and in a prospective sample of males, independent of traditional risk factors.

medical_qa.question: Do transient lower esophageal sphincter relaxations result from passive opening of the cardia by gastric distention?
medical_qa.normalized_answer: Transient lower esophageal sphincter relaxations occur before the gastroesophageal junction can open, refuting the hypothesis that they result from passive mechanical distraction of the gastroesophageal junction.

medical_qa.question: Does reg IV activate the epidermal growth factor receptor/Akt/AP-1 signaling pathway in colon adenocarcinomas?
medical_qa.normalized_answer: Reg IV activates the EGF receptor/Akt/AP-1 signaling pathway in colon adenocarcinomas.

medical_qa.question: Do myofibroblast matrix metalloproteinases activate the neutrophil chemoattractant CXCL7 from intestinal epithelial cells?
medical_qa.normalized_answer: MMPs induce the production of the neutrophil chemoattractant CXCL7 from intestinal epithelial cells, promoting immune activation.

medical_qa.question: Is discontinuation of treatment of schizophrenic patients driven by poor symptom response : a pooled post-hoc analysis of four atypical antipsychotic drugs?
medical_qa.normalized_answer: Discontinuation of treatment in schizophrenic patients was primarily due to poor response to treatment, worsening psychiatric symptoms, and to a lesser extent, medication intolerability. Adherence to treatment may improve with effective symptom control, leading to better long-term therapy outcomes.

medical_qa.question: Does the receptor-binding region of human apolipoprotein E have direct anti-infective activity?
medical_qa.normalized_answer: Human apolipoprotein E or fragments with the receptor-binding domain may help innate immunity to viral infection by disrupting viral particles or inhibiting viral attachment, reducing viral entry.

medical_qa.question: Does low-dose radiation plus rapamycin promote long-term bone marrow chimerism?
medical_qa.normalized_answer: Rapamycin in combination with low-dose radiation promoted long-term bone marrow chimerism in a murine model without apparent toxicity.

medical_qa.question: Is plasma apolipoprotein E concentration an important determinant of phospholipid transfer protein activity in type 2 diabetes mellitus?
medical_qa.normalized_answer: Plasma apolipoprotein E concentration is an important regulator of phospholipid transfer protein activity, particularly in type 2 diabetes mellitus.

medical_qa.question: Is left atrial index a predictor of exercise capacity in patients with hypertrophic cardiomyopathy?
medical_qa.normalized_answer: Left atrial volume index was independently associated with exercise capacity in patients with hypertrophic cardiomyopathy.

medical_qa.question: Is a low blood ethanol level associated with improved cytokine production in aged mice after traumatic injury?
medical_qa.normalized_answer: Low levels of ethanol at the time of injury are associated with partial restoration of immune responses in aged mice.

medical_qa.question: Does tranexamic acid prevent rebleeding in an uncontrolled hemorrhage porcine model?
medical_qa.normalized_answer: Tranexamic acid did not reduce rebleeding events, blood loss, or mortality in uncontrolled aortic hemorrhage.

medical_qa.question: Does alcohol consumption during gestation reduce the histamine and triiodothyronine content of rat immune cells?
medical_qa.normalized_answer: Alcohol consumption during early pregnancy in rats decreased histamine and triiodothyronine content in peritoneal immune cells of adult offspring, but had no effect on thymic cells.

medical_qa.question: Are preoperative serum tissue factor levels an independent prognostic factor in patients with ovarian carcinoma?
medical_qa.normalized_answer: Preoperative serum TF levels are significantly elevated in patients with ovarian carcinoma. Elevated preoperative TF level is an independent prognostic factor for death from disease.

medical_qa.question: Does Intravenous oxygen therapy increase the activity of the antioxidative and antiatherogenic serum enzyme paraoxonase 1?
medical_qa.normalized_answer: Intravenous oxygen therapy increases serum PON1 activity, suggesting an adaptation to oxidative stress and a potential mechanism for the protective effects of this therapy.

medical_qa.question: Is tissue-type plasminogen activator activity in morphologically normal tissues adjacent to gastrointestinal carcinomas associated with the degree of tumor progression?
medical_qa.normalized_answer: Tissue-type plasminogen activator (t-PA) activity in morphologically normal tissues adjacent to gastrointestinal carcinomas is associated with the degree of tumor progression.

medical_qa.question: Does bispectral index monitoring improve early recovery of geriatric outpatients undergoing brief surgical procedures?
medical_qa.normalized_answer: The use of BIS monitoring for titrating sevoflurane in elderly outpatients undergoing brief surgical procedures did not improve early recovery.

medical_qa.question: Does chronic aspiration of gastric fluid accelerate pulmonary allograft dysfunction in a rat model of lung transplantation?
medical_qa.normalized_answer: Chronic aspiration of gastric contents accelerates pulmonary allograft dysfunction in a rat model of lung transplantation, promoting a profibrotic environment.

medical_qa.question: Does dexamethasone reduce reintubation rate due to postextubation stridor in a high-risk paediatric population?
medical_qa.normalized_answer: Dexamethasone was found effective in preventing reintubation due to postextubation stridor in a high-risk pediatric population aged between 4 weeks and 6 years with intubation exceeding 24 hours.

medical_qa.question: Do thermal injury-induced peroxynitrite production and pulmonary inducible nitric oxide synthase expression depend on JNK/AP-1 signaling?
medical_qa.normalized_answer: Thermal injury induces lung tissue JNK activation and AP-1 DNA-binding activity mainly from airway epithelial cells. JNK inhibition decreases thermal injury-induced lung neutrophil infiltration and subsequently pulmonary hyperpermeability.

medical_qa.question: Does vascular endothelial growth factor naked DNA gene transfer enhance thrombus recanalization and resolution?
medical_qa.normalized_answer: VEGF gene therapy resulted in smaller thrombi with greater recanalization, suggesting it may improve the resolution of venous thrombi.

medical_qa.question: Does cytoregR inhibit growth and proliferation of human adenocarcinoma cells via induction of apoptosis?
medical_qa.normalized_answer: CytoregR inhibits growth in human cancer cells through apoptosis induction via the CPP32 death pathway, showing no significant effect on normal cells.

medical_qa.question: Does activation of soluble guanylate cyclase reverse experimental pulmonary hypertension and vascular remodeling?
medical_qa.normalized_answer: Activation of sGC reverses hemodynamic and structural changes associated with monocrotaline- and chronic hypoxia-induced experimental pulmonary hypertension. This effect is partially dependent on endogenous nitric oxide generated by NOS3.

medical_qa.question: Does autologous myoblast transplantation after myocardial infarction increase the inducibility of ventricular arrhythmias?
medical_qa.normalized_answer: Myoblast transplantation in an infarcted rat model induced electrical ventricular instability, leading to increased susceptibility to ventricular arrhythmias during programmed electrical stimulation.

medical_qa.question: Does eradication of small intestinal bacterial overgrowth in the cystic fibrosis mouse reduce mucus accumulation?
medical_qa.normalized_answer: Eradication of bacterial overgrowth in CF mice significantly decreased mucus secretion and accumulation in intestinal crypts without affecting mucin gene expression.

medical_qa.question: Do dietary gangliosides enhance in vitro lipid uptake in weanling rats?
medical_qa.normalized_answer: The study found that feeding a GANG-enriched diet to weanling rats did not alter weight gain or intestinal morphology. Enhanced uptake of stearic acid in the ileum and stearic and linoleic acid in the jejunum was observed, possibly due to a modification in physical properties of the brush border membrane.

medical_qa.question: Are small increases in extravascular lung water accurately detected by transpulmonary thermodilution?
medical_qa.normalized_answer: Transpulmonary thermodilution accurately detects small increases in extravascular lung water, potentially allowing for the precise diagnosis of incipient pulmonary edema.

medical_qa.question: Is elevated plasma phospholipid transfer protein activity a determinant of carotid intima-media thickness in type 2 diabetes mellitus?
medical_qa.normalized_answer: Yes, elevated plasma phospholipid transfer protein (PLTP) activity is positively associated with carotid intima-media thickness (IMT) in type 2 diabetes mellitus.

medical_qa.question: Is infection with Chlamydia pneumoniae but not Helicobacter pylori related to elevated apolipoprotein B levels?
medical_qa.normalized_answer: Infection with Chlamydia pneumoniae, but not Helicobacter pylori, was associated with increased apolipoprotein B levels.

medical_qa.question: Does the PTEN tumor suppressor inhibit telomerase activity in endometrial cancer cells by decreasing hTERT mRNA levels?
medical_qa.normalized_answer: PTEN may regulate telomerase activity by inhibiting Akt activation, leading to decreased hTERT mRNA levels in endometrial cancer cells.

medical_qa.question: Does effect of curing regime on the cytotoxicity of resin-modified glass-ionomer lining cement applied to an odontoblast-cell line?
medical_qa.normalized_answer: Light-curing reduces the cytotoxicity of Fuji Lining LC. Following the manufacturer's recommended light-curing regime may prevent toxic effects on pulp cells.

medical_qa.question: Do aurothiomalate and hydroxychloroquine inhibit nitric oxide production in chondrocytes and in human osteoarthritic cartilage?
medical_qa.normalized_answer: Aurothiomalate and hydroxychloroquine suppressed IL-1beta-induced NO production in chondrocyte cultures and in OA cartilage.

medical_qa.question: Is syndecan-1 expression upregulated in degenerating articular cartilage in a transgenic mouse model for osteoarthritis?
medical_qa.normalized_answer: Syndecan-1 expression is upregulated in articular cartilage during early stages of cartilage degeneration in a transgenic mouse model for osteoarthritis.

medical_qa.question: Do urinary excretions of lipocalin-type prostaglandin D2 synthase predict the development of proteinuria and renal injury in OLETF rats?
medical_qa.normalized_answer: Urinary excretions of L-PGDS in OLETF rats are likely indicative of increased glomerular permeability and may predict future glomerular damage associated with diabetes.

medical_qa.question: Does absence of chx10 cause neural progenitors to persist in the adult retina?
medical_qa.normalized_answer: In the absence of Chx10, proliferative expansion of embryonic retinal progenitor cells is reduced. In the adult retina, lack of Chx10 leads to a population of dividing neural progenitor cells that persist and generate new neurons in the central retina.

medical_qa.question: Does prevalence of negative chest radiography result in the emergency department patient with decompensated heart failure?
medical_qa.normalized_answer: Approximately 1 of every 5 patients admitted from the ED with acute decompensated heart failure had no signs of congestion on chest radiography. Patients lacking signs of congestion on ED chest radiography were more likely to have an ED non-heart failure diagnosis than patients with signs of congestion. Clinicians should not rule out heart failure in patients with no radiographic signs of congestion.

medical_qa.question: Does aprotinin inhibit proinflammatory activation of endothelial cells by thrombin through the protease-activated receptor 1?
medical_qa.normalized_answer: Aprotinin inhibits endothelial cell activation by thrombin and downstream inflammatory responses in vitro by blocking protease-activated receptor 1.

medical_qa.question: Does endoscopic ultrasonography-identified celiac adenopathy remain a poor prognostic factor despite preoperative chemoradiotherapy in esophageal adenocarcinoma?
medical_qa.normalized_answer: Endoscopic ultrasonography-identified celiac adenopathy in patients with adenocarcinoma of the distal esophagus is associated with decreased long-term survival despite preoperative chemoradiotherapy. Induction chemotherapy before concurrent chemoradiotherapy and surgical intervention may improve survival in this high-risk group.

medical_qa.question: Are connexin43 levels increased in mouse neural crest cells exposed to homocysteine?
medical_qa.normalized_answer: Yes, connexin43 levels were found to be increased in mouse neural crest cells exposed to homocysteine, suggesting a potential role in the embryotoxic effects of homocysteine.

medical_qa.question: Does beta2-adrenergic agonist protect human endothelial cells from hypoxia/reoxygenation injury in vitro?
medical_qa.normalized_answer: Formoterol reduces endothelial cell death and reactive oxygen species production in an in vitro hypoxia/reoxygenation model, mediated by beta2-adrenergic receptors and partially by nitric oxide synthase.

medical_qa.question: Does thromboxane A2/prostaglandin H2 receptor activation mediate angiotensin II-induced postischemic neovascularization?
medical_qa.normalized_answer: Endogenous activation of TXA2 receptor did not affect spontaneous neovascularization in ischemia, but it is involved in Ang II-induced vessel growth through AT1 receptor.

medical_qa.question: Is atherosclerosis in mice affected by a reduction in tissue factor expression?
medical_qa.normalized_answer: Reducing tissue factor expression by 50% in all cells or selectively in hematopoietic cell-derived TF does not impact the development of atherosclerotic lesions in mice.

medical_qa.question: Does 3,4-Methylenedioxymethamphetamine enhance the release of acetylcholine in the prefrontal cortex and dorsal hippocampus of the rat?
medical_qa.normalized_answer: MDMA increases acetylcholine release in the prefrontal cortex and dorsal hippocampus of rats, possibly involving serotonergic and dopaminergic mechanisms.

medical_qa.question: Does age influence the emm type distribution of pediatric group A streptococcal pharyngeal isolates?
medical_qa.normalized_answer: Age-related changes in emm type distribution of pharyngeal group A streptococcal isolates are present in childhood.

medical_qa.question: Are parkin-deficient mice more sensitive to 6-hydroxydopamine or methamphetamine neurotoxicity?
medical_qa.normalized_answer: Parkin-deficient mice are not more sensitive to dopaminergic neurotoxicity from treatment with METH or 6-OHDA.
